{
  "page": "Dawn",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Ser_Arthur_Dayne_by_henning.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/65/Ser_Arthur_Dayne_by_henning.jpg/350px-Ser_Arthur_Dayne_by_henning.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"292\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/65/Ser_Arthur_Dayne_by_henning.jpg/525px-Ser_Arthur_Dayne_by_henning.jpg 1.5x, /images/6/65/Ser_Arthur_Dayne_by_henning.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Ser_Arthur_Dayne_by_henning.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Dawn, wielded by <a href=\"/index.php/Arthur_Dayne\" title=\"Arthur Dayne\">Arthur Dayne</a>. By Henning Ludvigsen © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Dawn</b> is the famous ancestral <a href=\"/index.php/Greatsword\" title=\"Greatsword\">greatsword</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Dayne\" title=\"House Dayne\">House Dayne</a>, whose wielder is given the title <a href=\"/index.php/Sword_of_the_Morning\" title=\"Sword of the Morning\">Sword of the Morning</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Description\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Description</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Origin\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Origin</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Arthur_Dayne\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Arthur Dayne</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#A_Game_of_Thrones\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#Behind_the_Scenes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Behind the Scenes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Description\">Description</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dawn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Description\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Dayne.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/95/House_Dayne.svg/350px-House_Dayne.svg.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"350\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/95/House_Dayne.svg/525px-House_Dayne.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/9/95/House_Dayne.svg/700px-House_Dayne.svg.png 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Dayne.svg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The sigil of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Dayne\" title=\"House Dayne\">House Dayne</a>, depicting Dawn and a falling star.</div></div></div>\n<div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">See also: <a href=\"/index.php/Category:Images_of_Dawn\" title=\"Category:Images of Dawn\">Images of Dawn</a></div>\n<p>Dawn is a greatsword.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Its blade is as pale as milkglass,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> unlike dark <a href=\"/index.php/Valyrian_steel\" title=\"Valyrian steel\">Valyrian steel</a>, but is similar in strength and sharpness.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafdorne:_the_andals_arrive.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafdorne:_the_andals_arrive.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Per legend, it was forged from the heart of a <a href=\"/index.php/Astronomy\" title=\"Astronomy\">fallen star</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> likely <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meteoric_iron\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Meteoric iron\">meteoric iron</a>. The <a href=\"/index.php/Coat_of_arms\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Coat of arms\">coat of arms</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Dayne\" title=\"House Dayne\">House Dayne</a> depicts the white sword and falling star.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Unlike other houses who have ancestral swords, House Dayne does not pass its sword from <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Starfall\" title=\"Lord of Starfall\">lord</a> to heir. Only a <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knight</a> of House Dayne who is deemed worthy can wield Dawn, and the <a href=\"/index.php/Sword_of_the_Morning\" title=\"Sword of the Morning\">Sword of the Morning</a> is envied throughout the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafdorne:_the_andals_arrive.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafdorne:_the_andals_arrive.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dawn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Origin\">Origin</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dawn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Origin\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Jose_Daniel_Cabrera_PenaSwordOfTheMorning.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/f3/Jose_Daniel_Cabrera_PenaSwordOfTheMorning.jpg/350px-Jose_Daniel_Cabrera_PenaSwordOfTheMorning.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"877\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/f3/Jose_Daniel_Cabrera_PenaSwordOfTheMorning.jpg/525px-Jose_Daniel_Cabrera_PenaSwordOfTheMorning.jpg 1.5x, /images/f/f3/Jose_Daniel_Cabrera_PenaSwordOfTheMorning.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Jose_Daniel_Cabrera_PenaSwordOfTheMorning.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>A <a href=\"/index.php/Sword_of_the_Morning\" title=\"Sword of the Morning\">Sword of the Morning</a> gripping the hilt of Dawn, by Jose Daniel Cabrera © for <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i></div></div></div>\n<p>According to legend, the founder of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Dayne\" title=\"House Dayne\">House Dayne</a> tracked a falling star to an island at the mouth of the <a href=\"/index.php/Torentine\" title=\"Torentine\">Torentine</a>. He discovered there a stone with magical powers, and the castle of <a href=\"/index.php/Starfall\" title=\"Starfall\">Starfall</a> was constructed on that spot.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafdorne:_kingdoms_of_the_first_men.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafdorne:_kingdoms_of_the_first_men.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> The greatsword Dawn was forged from the heart of this fallen star,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> and has possibly been wielded by Daynes for ten thousand years.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Arthur_Dayne\">Arthur Dayne</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dawn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Arthur Dayne\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The last known wielder of Dawn was Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Arthur_Dayne\" title=\"Arthur Dayne\">Arthur Dayne</a>, a chivalrous knight in the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Aerys_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aerys II Targaryen\">Aerys II Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aerys_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aerys_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> The <a href=\"/index.php/Smiling_Knight\" title=\"Smiling Knight\">Smiling Knight</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingswood_Brotherhood\" title=\"Kingswood Brotherhood\">Kingswood Brotherhood</a> tried to claim Dawn from Arthur through combat, but the <a href=\"/index.php/Robber_knight\" title=\"Robber knight\">robber knight</a> was killed by the Sword of the Morning.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> Arthur granted knighthood to <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a> after the battle. When Arthur tapped Dawn on the youth's shoulder, the blade went through Jaime's tunic and caused him to bleed.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After Arthur died in <a href=\"/index.php/Combat_at_the_tower_of_joy\" title=\"Combat at the tower of joy\">combat at the tower of joy</a> during <a href=\"/index.php/Robert%27s_Rebellion\" title=\"Robert&#39;s Rebellion\">Robert's Rebellion</a>, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Eddard_Stark\" title=\"Eddard Stark\">Eddard Stark</a> rode to Starfall to deliver Dawn to Arthur's sister, <a href=\"/index.php/Ashara_Dayne\" title=\"Ashara Dayne\">Ashara Dayne</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafdorne:_the_andals_arrive.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafdorne:_the_andals_arrive.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dawn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Game_of_Thrones\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dawn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Game of Thrones\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>At the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Keep\" title=\"Red Keep\">Red Keep</a>, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Eddard_Stark\" title=\"Eddard Stark\">Eddard Stark</a> has a fever dream, which includes Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Arthur_Dayne\" title=\"Arthur Dayne\">Arthur Dayne</a> wielding Dawn at the <a href=\"/index.php/Tower_of_joy\" title=\"Tower of joy\">tower of joy</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dawn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The blade was pale as milkglass, alive with light.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Eddard_Stark\" title=\"Eddard Stark\">Eddard Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The finest knight I ever saw was Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Arthur_Dayne\" title=\"Arthur Dayne\">Arthur Dayne</a>, who fought with a blade called Dawn, forged from the heart of a <a href=\"/index.php/Astronomy\" title=\"Astronomy\">fallen star</a>. They called him the <a href=\"/index.php/Sword_of_the_Morning\" title=\"Sword of the Morning\">Sword of the Morning</a>, and he would have killed me but for <a href=\"/index.php/Howland_Reed\" title=\"Howland Reed\">Howland Reed</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Eddard_Stark\" title=\"Eddard Stark\">Eddard Stark</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">Bran Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Smiling Knight</b>: It's that white sword of yours I want.<br />\n<b>Arthur</b>: Then you shall have it, ser.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;The <a href=\"/index.php/Smiling_Knight\" title=\"Smiling Knight\">Smiling Knight</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Arthur_Dayne\" title=\"Arthur Dayne\">Arthur Dayne</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Oh, I'd say Dawn goes back a couple thousand years... and before that, things get a little fuzzy anyway.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rssm1183.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rssm1183.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Dawn remains at <a href=\"/index.php/Starfall\" title=\"Starfall\">Starfall</a>, until another <a href=\"/index.php/Sword_of_the_Morning\" title=\"Sword of the Morning\">Sword of the Morning</a> shall arise.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rssm1193.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rssm1193.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Behind_the_Scenes\">Behind the Scenes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dawn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Behind the Scenes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/House_Dayne\" title=\"House Dayne\">House Dayne</a>'s sword Dawn may have been inspired by several fictional swords:\n</p>\n<ul><li>The <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ebony_Blade\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Ebony Blade\">Ebony Blade</a>, a sword carved from a fallen meteor and wielded by <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Black_Knight_(Dane_Whitman)\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Black Knight (Dane Whitman)\">Dane Whitman</a>, a comic book superhero known as the Black Knight. <a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a> grew up a fan of Marvel Comics, including the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Avengers_(comics)\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Avengers (comics)\">Avengers</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-13\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Sorrow and Thorn, two swords from the <i><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Memory,_Sorrow,_and_Thorn\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Memory, Sorrow, and Thorn\">Memory, Sorrow, and Thorn</a></i> series of Martin's colleague <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tad_Williams\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Tad Williams\">Tad Williams</a>. Sorrow was forged by the Sithi, a race of immortal human-like beings also known as the \"Dawn Children\", while Thorn was created from a piece of a sky-stone.<sup id=\"cite_ref-14\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Excalibur\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Excalibur\">Excalibur</a>, the mythical sword wielded by <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/King_Arthur\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:King Arthur\">King Arthur</a>, a central figure in the medieval literary tradition known as the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matter_of_Britain\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Matter of Britain\">Matter of Britain</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-15\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>The swords <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://lotr.fandom.com/wiki/Anglachel\">Anglachel</a> and <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://lotr.fandom.com/wiki/Anguirel\">Anguirel</a> from <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Middle_Earth\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Middle Earth\">Middle Earth</a>, blades forged of meteoric iron. <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/J._R._R._Tolkien\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:J. R. R. Tolkien\">J. R. R. Tolkien</a> is a known influence to Martin.<sup id=\"cite_ref-16\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-16\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<p>When asked which sword he would wield if he could, Martin said he would choose Dawn.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rssm16123.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_17-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rssm16123.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-17\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dawn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Ragot39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\">1.4</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A